news.title: Panaji's ODP for 2031 will get GIS-based zoning plan
news.para: “The draft ODP of the Panaji planning area has already been prepared by the North Goa Planning and Development Authority, and is approved by the government,” a senior official said.

news.title: Wait on for Haryana assembly nod on HSVP schemes
news.para: Unlike previous years, when LAO had to go through a long process for acquisition of land, the HSVP would be this time going through a land-pooling policy to acquire the land.

news.title: No rooftop solar plants? Be ready to face action
news.para: In a letter to the deputy commissioner-cum-estate officer, the Crest has stated, “Action deemed fit may be initiated against defaulting residential houses who have not installed solar power plants till date.”

news.title: Haryana government refuses proposed CHB luxury towers at IT Park
news.para: The CHB had also written to the Punjab government and PGI about the residential towers but no communication has been received from them.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board bats for vastu-friendly properties
news.para: Officials said, there has been a huge demand among prospective buyers to buy Vastu compliant properties and most private builders are constructing Vastu-friendly properties.

news.title: Mumbai: Relief for 24,000 Mhada tenants, two-fold rent hike scrapped
news.para: Fadnavis further said that the state government will come out with an amnesty scheme for those who have not paid rent and have been sent notices to pay rent, with a penalty and interest over the due amount.

news.title: Gujarat: Credit demand spikes as developers scramble to beat year-end, jantri deadlines
news.para: They are also scrambling to complete deals before the end of the financial year. They are borrowing from financial institutions and private financiers to go ahead with projects and ensure registration of new land purchases.

news.title: Gurugram: 'Lifts faulty for months', BPTP Spacio flat owners go to police
news.para: Residents complained about faulty lifts jeopardising their safety and demanded a concrete solution. They said the automatic rescue devices of these lifts fail often and cause sudden falls from a considerable height.

news.title: DTCP razes five illegal colonies in Gurugram, frees up 12 acres
news.para: During the demolition drive, the team razed unauthorised structures, road networks, and boundary walls. The officials also directed locals to not invest in such colonies without checking their status with the department.

news.title: Adani Group prepays another $500 million loan for Ambuja cement
news.para: ​In a statement, Adani group said it has repaid USD 2.15 billion of loans that were taken by pledging shares in the conglomerate's listed firms and also another USD 500 million in loans taken for the acquisition of Ambuja Cement.

news.title: L&T sells three pre-leased floors in Powai office tower to National Realty for Rs 81 crore
news.para: The company sold this office with nearly 37,527 sq ft carpet area immediately after leasing it to CitiusTech Healthcare Technology at starting annual rent of Rs 7.40 crore.

news.title: Why 2.5 lakh flats' registries are stuck in Noida
news.para: For long, homebuyers had pinned hopes on the apex court judgment related to the rate of land dues, anticipating that builders will clear their dues as per the court order and the registry of flats will finally start.

news.title: Many haven't shifted to new flats yet, but Noida authority starts demolition of slums
news.para: The move comes nearly three years after the Authority allotted 2,064 newly-built flats in Sector 122 to slum residents under the jhuggi jhopri rehabilitation scheme.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA commences e-registration of flats from its premises
news.para: Aiming to boost e-registration of flats from developer’s office training was given to builders and software was shared so that developers could carry out registration of new flats from its own offices.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body likely to fall short of Rs 2,000 crore property tax target
news.para: So far, the GHMC has earned 1,522 crore in revenue through property tax. While bill collectors have been pressed into action to collect arrears from property owners, officials remain sceptical of achieving the remaining 478 crore target in 20 days.
